This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes new neural network components for performing arithmetic operations. It also draws inspiration from a theoretical analysis of recently proposed arithmetic components, which is a common approach in machine learning research. 

It could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it specifically focuses on neural network components. 

Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as neural networks are a popular tool in AI research. 

The paper also mentions using the proposed components for tasks such as image classification (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL), so it could potentially be categorized under those sub-categories as well.
